
[1]lofty

   LOFTY, a.

   1. Elevated in place; high; as a lofty tower; a lofty mountain. [But it
   expresses more than high, or at least is more emphatical, poetical and
   elegant.]

   See lofty Lebanon his head advance.

   2. Elevated in condition or character.

   Thus saith the high and lofty One, that inhabiteth eternity, whose name
   is Holy - Is. 57.

   3. Proud; haughty; as lofty looks. Is. 2.

   4. Elevated in sentiment or diction; sublime; as lofty strains; lofty
   rhyme.

   5. Stately; dignified; as lofty steps.
